<doc f='codebrowser/code/opusfile-0.8/src/internal.h' l='104'>/*Advance a file offset by the given amount, clamping against OP_INT64_MAX.
  This is used to advance a known offset by things like OP_CHUNK_SIZE or
   OP_PAGE_SIZE_MAX, while making sure to avoid signed overflow.
  It assumes that both _offset and _amount are non-negative.*/</doc>
